Name: Conclave
Description: The Conclave is the representative of Aiur's Protoss power, and its assembled tribal elders play a decisive role in the development of Protoss. You can apply for the protocols of different tribes in the parliament to strengthen different troops. There will be mutual exclusion, which makes the application of multiple councils may reduce the combat capability of some units. But once the meeting is successfully coordinated, your army's combat capability will be greatly improved.

Root.Tooltip: Drops the current order without performing it, and allows you to select a different order.
Root.Name: Cancel

Root.Tooltip: Cancels construction of this structure, destroying the structure and giving a partial refund.
Root.Name: Cancel

Root.Tooltip: Drops the current order without performing it, and allows you to select a different order.
Root.Name: Cancel

Root.Tooltip: Deploy a Pylon and Aiur Council Guards at target location. Council Guards includes two zealots and two dragoons.
Root.Name: Council Guard: Aiur

Root.Tooltip: Deploy a Dark Pylon and Nerazim Council Guards at target location. Council Guards includes two Dark Templars and two Corsairs.
Root.Name: Council Guard: Nerazim

Root.Tooltip:
Apply for assistance from executor **Nahaan**. As the leader of the Ara tribal council, Nahaan's troops are all composed of Aiur's bravest fighters. Once you apply for the Ara protocol, your **Zealots and Dragoons** will be strengthened, and you can deploy a Ara front-line unit on the battlefield. You can unlock related upgrades in **Adun Council and Forge**

Ara protocol enhancement:
1. The health value and shield value of fanatics and dragoons are greatly increased.
2. Zealots can use charge, and the Dragoons gains extra attack range.
3. The construction time of Pylon is reduced by 50%, and the supply provided is increased by 100%. You can unlock and upgrade in the Forge to greatly improve the ability of friendly units within the Pylon range.
4. You can deploy a pylon anywhere in the battlefield, and warp two Zealots and two Dragons.
5. Each time your Probe collects minerals, it will bring back a little extra resources.

Ara protocol conflict:
1. Your Nerazim units, Corsairs, Dark Templars, and Void Rays, consume 100% more resources in production.
2. The application time of other leaders' parliamentary agreements is increased by 30 seconds, and the cost is increased by 100/100.
Root.Name: Execute Protocol: Ara

Root.Tooltip:
Apply for assistance from executor **Mohandar**. As the leader of the Nerazim tribal council, his warriors are subordinate to the Dark Templars of the Shakuras. Once you apply for the Nerazim agreement, your Corsairs, Void Rays and Dark Templars will be strengthened, and you can deploy a Nerazim front-line unit on the battlefield. You can unlock related upgrades in **Dark Shrine and Fleet Beacon**

Nerazim protocol enhancement:
1. The gas consumed by Corsairs, Void Rays and Dark Templars is reduced by 50 points.
2. The Corsair's weapon is replaced with High-energy Neutron and can use Disruption Web. The Dark Templar can use Blink and will be recalled to the Dark Shrine when dying. The Void Ray will cause additional damage to heavy armor units.
3. Attack damage and movement speed of Corsairs, Dark Templars and Void Rays by 25% and 50%.
4. You can deploy a dark pylon anywhere in the battlefield, and warp two Dark Templars and two Corsairs.

Nerazim protocol conflict:
1. Except for the unit Corsairs, Dark Templars and Void Rays of Nerazim, the production price of other units is increased by 100%.
2. The application time of other leaders' parliamentary agreements is increased by 30 seconds, and the cost is increased by 100/100.
Root.Name: Execute Protocol: Nerazim

Root.Tooltip:
Apply for assistance from executor **Tabrenus**. Tabrenus is a representative of the Khalai class phase technicians. Once you apply for the Furinax agreement, your Immortals, Reavers, and Colossus will be strengthened. You can unlock related upgrades in **Robotics Support Bay**

Furinax protocol enhancement:
1. Reduce the unit cost of the Robotics Facility by 20%.
2. The damage absorbed by the Immortal barrier is increased by 100%, the sputtering range of Reaver attack is increased, and the technology of passive loading of Colossus improves the range.
3. The mechanical unit can repair itself slowly.

Furinax protocol conflict:
1. Every time the Probe occupies 1 point of supply, it will reduce the attack speed of other non mechanical units by 0.33%.
2. The application time of other leaders' parliamentary agreements is increased by 30 seconds, and the cost is increased by 100/100.
Root.Name: Execute Protocol: Finax

Root.Tooltip:
Apply for assistance from executor **Urun**. Urun is the leader of the Auriga tribe, which is good at making star ships and war vehicles. Once you apply for the Auriga agreement, your **Scouts and Carriers** will be strengthened. You can unlock related upgrades in **Fleet Beacon**

Auriga protocol enhancement:
1. Reduce the units in Stargate by 20% of its warp time.
2. The Scout obtains additional attack range, and the Carrier automatically loads the gravitational ejection technology.
3. The Shield of Aiur can use Planetary Cracker to destroy all units in the target area.

Auriga protocol conflict:
1. Your ground unit receives 30% extra damage.
2. The application time of other leaders' parliamentary agreements is increased by 30 seconds, and the cost is increased by 100/100.
Root.Name: Execute Protocol: Origa

Root.Tooltip:
Apply for assistance from executor **Kalram**. Kalram is a High Templar representing the Akilae tribe. Once you apply for the Akilae agreement, your High Templars, Archons and Arbiters will be strengthened. You can unlock related upgrades in **Templar Archive and Fleet Beacon**

Akilae protocol enhancement:
1. Your psionic unit energy recovery and skill cooldown are reduced by 50%, and teammates can enjoy half of the bonus.
2. Archons, High Templars and Arbiters will gain full energy once they have finished production.
3. The time for High Templars to merge as Archons has been reduced from 10 seconds to 1 second.
4. High Templars and Archons cast range increased by 50%.
5. Each time your Probe collects gas, it will bring back a little extra resources.

Akilae protocol conflict:
1. The attack damage of all mechanical units is reduced by 20%.
2. The application time of other leaders' parliamentary agreements is increased by 30 seconds, and the cost is increased by 100/100.
Root.Name: Execute Protocol: Akilae

Root.Tooltip:
Apply for assistance from executor **Zekrath**. Zekrath is the representative of Shalek tribe and the protector of ancient knowledge of Protoss. Shalek will give you great benefits in technology development and unit operations.

Shalek protocol enhancement:
1. Except for council application, the resource consumption and time required for all research projects will be reduced by 50%.
2. The construction time of all production and research buildings is reduced by 50%, and the gas consumption is reduced by 50%.
3. Your attack upgrade and defense upgrade in Forge and Cybernetics Core can be unlocked to the fifth level.

Shalek protocol conflict:
1. Reduce your supply ceiling by 50 points.
2. The application time of other leaders' parliamentary agreements is increased by 30 seconds, and the cost is increased by 100/100.
Root.Name: Execute Protocol: Shelak
